        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 4:41PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 441 PM CDT/341 PM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of
strong thunderstorms 11 miles west of Red Bluff Reservoir, or 32
miles west of Mentone, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Red Bluff Reservoir, Orla, and Red Bluff.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT/900 PM MDT/ for
southeastern New Mexico.</instruction>
